<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-11-08"><hi rend="italic">November 8,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to thank you for
                            your note of this day’s date concerning the projected visit to
                            Washington of Sir W. Laurier and Sir L. Davies.</p>
                        <p>As regards the last paragraph of your note, I would observe that there is
                            no intention whatsoever to modify the character of the meeting, and that
                            the experts will, of course, report upon the condition of the seal herd,
                            as originally arranged.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>